
For using the Maven repository one needs to add the following repository into the settings.xml or the project pom:

<repository>
	<id>oss-sonatype</id>
	<snapshots>
		<enabled>true</enabled>
	</snapshots>
	<url>https://oss.sonatype.org/content/repositories/snapshots/</url>
</repository>

Now create a new project and add 
<dependency>
	<groupId>com.jme3</groupId>
	<artifactId>bullet</artifactId>
	<version>3.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
	<type>pom</type>
</dependency>
to your dependencies and start coding :)

Running the demos:
check out jme-demo-test and run "mvn exec:java"

Using the archetypes:
mvn archetype:generate -DarchetypeCatalog=http://oss.sonatype.org/service/local/repositories/snapshots/content/


To use the deployment-script one needs to add the following server config to settings.xml.
(NOTE: Deployment requires a Sonatype-JIRA-User with access to teh repository, contact pflanzenmoerder for details)
<server>
	<id>jme3-sonatype</id>
	<username><JIRA-Username></username>
	<password><JIRA-Password></password>
</server>

